name: Linda Hallmark
text: I haven't been to the fair in years and it is different, smaller. but still entertaining. Something for everyone to enjoy. I have to say they have alot of rides for big kids and little ones. The elephant show and trapeze show was great because we were within feet of the action!  Don't miss the Puppets and the petting zoo, but watch out for baby camel bc he likes to snuggle! We suggest buying the ride pass for $25 and just ride everything until you get dizzy and fall down. The parking is very close  to the entrance, it was clean, the rides were in great condition, people were friendly given the heat, not once did we feel unsafe!  Plenty of "fair" food available! Once the sun went down, the lights and music make it seem more like the old Alabama State Fair minus the livestock area.
